Object.Field:
This mapping uses Oracle Partition Exchange to perform incremental upload operations for a given partition using the IKM Oracle Partition Exchange.
The partitioned table is used as a source table, and it has been aliased as W_ORDERS_F_AS_OF_TODAY. The Partition/Subpartition property of the W_ORDERS_F_AS_OF_TODAY has been configured with an ODI variable, PARTITION_MONTH, to set the partition name dynamically and select data from a given partition.
The mapping uses the SET component to combine the newly source dataset with the existing data of a given partition in the W_ORDERS_F_AS_OF_TODAY table. The Set component uses the UNION operator to combine the existing data of a given partition with the incremental source dataset.
The partition exchange operation replaces the entire partition of the target partitioned table with the content of the ODI flow table, which includes the existing data from a given partition of the source partitioned table (W_ORDERS_F_AS_OF_TODAY) and the incoming new source dataset from the source table, MY_STG_AREA.ORDERS.
To test this mapping, perform the following steps:
1. Perform a full load of the partitioned table using any of the packages found under the folder "01 - Initial Load Samples". 2. Delete or truncate MY_STG_AREA.ORDERS table. 3. Add new data into the MY_STG_AREA.ORDERS for a given partition, and run this mapping. 4. You can use the INCREMENTAL.SQL script provided in the sample repository zip file to add additional data for a given partition. 5. Once you add additional data for a given partition, execute this mapping. 5. You should see that the mapping performs a union between the existing data in the partitioned table with the new data added in the MY_STG_AREA.ORDERS table. 6. The exchange operation replaces the entire partition with the new data set.
This mapping is ideal for incremental strategies. For instance, if your table has been partitioned by month, but you perform daily uploads, this mapping can append the daily uploads into a partition without losing the existing content of the partition.
